model.dbt_interview_project.stg_date.name: stg_date
model.dbt_interview_project.stg_date.rawCode:
WITH date_range AS (
    SELECT
        DATEADD(DAY, SEQ4(), DATE '2020-01-01') AS date
    FROM TABLE(GENERATOR(ROWCOUNT => 365*10)) -- 10 years of dates
)
SELECT
    date,
    EXTRACT(YEAR FROM date) AS year,
    EXTRACT(QUARTER FROM date) AS quarter,
    EXTRACT(MONTH FROM date) AS month,
    EXTRACT(DAY FROM date) AS day,
    EXTRACT(WEEK FROM date) AS week,
    EXTRACT(DAYOFWEEK FROM date) AS day_of_week,
    TO_VARCHAR(DAYNAME(date)) AS day_name,
    TO_VARCHAR(MONTHNAME(date)) AS month_name,
    CASE WHEN DAYOFWEEK(date) IN (0, 6) THEN TRUE ELSE FALSE END AS is_weekend,
    FALSE AS is_holiday
FROM date_range

model.dbt_interview_project.fct_intervie.name: fct_interview
model.dbt_interview_project.fct_intervie.rawCode:
{% set status_mappings = [
    {'status': 'REQUESTED',        'col': 'requested_datetime',         'agg': 'min'},
    {'status': 'SCHEDULED',        'col': 'scheduled_datetime',         'agg': 'min'},
    {'status': 'IN_PROGRESS',      'col': 'started_datetime',           'agg': 'min'},
    {'status': 'PENDING_FEEDBACK', 'col': 'pending_feedback_datetime',  'agg': 'min'},
    {'status': 'COMPLETED',        'col': 'feedback_provided_datetime', 'agg': 'min'},
    {'status': 'COMPLETED',        'col': 'finished_datetime',          'agg': 'max'},
    {'status': 'CANCELLED',        'col': 'cancelled_datetime',         'agg': 'max'}
] %}

WITH pivoted_timestamps AS (
    -- 12786 ID
    SELECT
      id,
      {% for mapping in status_mappings %}
        {{ mapping.agg }}(CASE WHEN status = '{{ mapping.status }}' THEN updated_at END) AS {{ mapping.col }}{{ "," if not loop.last }}
      {% endfor %}
    FROM {{ ref('stg_interview') }}
    GROUP BY 1
),

latest_interview_and_offset AS (
    SELECT 
      i.id,
      i.candidate_type,
      c.offset AS candidate_offset,
      i.status,
      e.offset AS interviewer_offset,
      i.location,
      i.is_logged,
      i.is_media_available,
      i.run_type,
      i.type,
      i.media_status,
      i.invite_answer_status,
      DATE(i.created_at) AS created_date,
      i.created_at AS created_datetime
    FROM {{ ref('latest_interview') }} i
      LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_candidate') }} c ON i.candidate_id = c.id AND i.created_at BETWEEN c._row_valid_from AND c._row_valid_to
        LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_employee') }} e ON i.interviewer_id = e.id AND i.created_at BETWEEN e._row_valid_from AND e._row_valid_to
),

joined AS (
    SELECT
      ls.*, -- columns with offset
      pt.requested_datetime,
      pt.scheduled_datetime,
      pt.started_datetime,
      pt.pending_feedback_datetime,
      pt.feedback_provided_datetime,
      pt.finished_datetime,
      pt.cancelled_datetime
    FROM latest_interview_and_offset ls
    LEFT JOIN pivoted_timestamps pt ON ls.id = pt.id
),

durations AS (
    SELECT *,
    -- Duration: ONLINE interviews only
        CASE 
            WHEN run_type = 'ONLINE' 
            THEN {{ dbt.datediff("started_datetime", "pending_feedback_datetime", "minute") }} 
        END AS interview_duration_minutes,
    
        {{ dbt.datediff("pending_feedback_datetime", "finished_datetime", "hour") }} AS feedback_delay_hours
    FROM joined

)

SELECT *
FROM durations
model.dbt_interview_project.fct_intervie.compiledCode:
WITH pivoted_timestamps AS (
    -- 12786 ID
    SELECT
      id,
      
        min(CASE WHEN status = 'REQUESTED' THEN updated_at END) AS requested_datetime,
      
        min(CASE WHEN status = 'SCHEDULED' THEN updated_at END) AS scheduled_datetime,
      
        min(CASE WHEN status = 'IN_PROGRESS' THEN updated_at END) AS started_datetime,
      
        min(CASE WHEN status = 'PENDING_FEEDBACK' THEN updated_at END) AS pending_feedback_datetime,
      
        min(CASE WHEN status = 'COMPLETED' THEN updated_at END) AS feedback_provided_datetime,
      
        max(CASE WHEN status = 'COMPLETED' THEN updated_at END) AS finished_datetime,
      
        max(CASE WHEN status = 'CANCELLED' THEN updated_at END) AS cancelled_datetime
      
    FROM DBT_PROJECT_DB.STG.stg_interview
    GROUP BY 1
),

latest_interview_and_offset AS (
    SELECT 
      i.id,
      i.candidate_type,
      c.offset AS candidate_offset,
      i.status,
      e.offset AS interviewer_offset,
      i.location,
      i.is_logged,
      i.is_media_available,
      i.run_type,
      i.type,
      i.media_status,
      i.invite_answer_status,
      DATE(i.created_at) AS created_date,
      i.created_at AS created_datetime
    FROM DBT_PROJECT_DB.STG.latest_interview i
      LEFT JOIN DBT_PROJECT_DB.STG.stg_candidate c ON i.candidate_id = c.id AND i.created_at BETWEEN c._row_valid_from AND c._row_valid_to
        LEFT JOIN DBT_PROJECT_DB.STG.stg_employee e ON i.interviewer_id = e.id AND i.created_at BETWEEN e._row_valid_from AND e._row_valid_to
),

joined AS (
    SELECT
      ls.*, -- columns with offset
      pt.requested_datetime,
      pt.scheduled_datetime,
      pt.started_datetime,
      pt.pending_feedback_datetime,
      pt.feedback_provided_datetime,
      pt.finished_datetime,
      pt.cancelled_datetime
    FROM latest_interview_and_offset ls
    LEFT JOIN pivoted_timestamps pt ON ls.id = pt.id
),

durations AS (
    SELECT *,
    -- Duration: ONLINE interviews only
        CASE 
            WHEN run_type = 'ONLINE' 
            THEN datediff(
        minute,
        started_datetime,
        pending_feedback_datetime
        ) 
        END AS interview_duration_minutes,
    
        datediff(
        hour,
        pending_feedback_datetime,
        finished_datetime
        ) AS feedback_delay_hours
    FROM joined

)

SELECT *
FROM durations
